interfaces.transform

Interface TransformInterface


  • public interface TransformInterface
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Learning Orchestra
    Summary:
    This interface is responsible for scikitlearn or tensorflow transformations, i.e., it runs any transformation algorithm of such tools transparently. It is important to understand that the transformed dataset cannot be opened by Learning Orchestra in the current version because each tool has its format particularities. On future versions we will try to enable content searches and consequently pagination for large datasets.

        com.google.gson.JsonObject runDatasetTransformSync(java.lang.String toolName,
                                                   java.lang.String datasetName,
                                                   java.lang.String description,
                                                   java.lang.String toolPackage,
                                                   java.lang.String toolClass,
                                                   java.util.Enumeration<java.lang.String> constructorParameters,
                                                   java.lang.String methodName,
                                                   java.util.Enumeration<java.lang.String> methodParameters)
        Parameters:
        toolName - represents the tool name, precisely scikit-learn or tensorflow
        datasetName - represents the name of the transformed dataset
        description - represents a description for the transform operation
        toolPackage - represents the tool transformation package. Ex. sklearn.preprocessing
        toolClass - represents the class of the used package. Ex. LabelEncoder
        constructorParameters - represents the constructors parameters, i.e., the arguments used to instantiate a class object
        methodName - represents the method of the class, which will be called. Ex. fit_transform
        methodParameters - represents the method parameters
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the dataset URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method runs any scikit-learn or tensorflow transformation method. The run operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.

      • await

      • deleteTransformSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject deleteTransformSync(java.lang.String datasetName)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - represents the dataset name
        Returns:
        a JSON object with an error message, a warning message or a correct delete message
        Summary:
        This method is responsible for deleting the dataset. This delete operation is synchronous, so it locks the caller until the deletion finished. If a dataset was used by another task (Ex. projection, histogram, pca, tune and so forth), it cannot be deleted.

      • deleteTransformAsync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject deleteTransformAsync(java.lang.String datasetName)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - represents the dataset name
        Returns:
        a JSON object with an error message, a warning message or a correct delete message
        Summary:
        This method is responsible for deleting the dataset. This delete operation is asynchronous, so it does not lock the caller until the deletion finished. Instead, it returns a JSON object with a URL for a future use. The caller uses the URL for delete checks. If a dataset was used by another task (Ex. projection, histogram, pca, tune and so forth), it cannot be deleted.

      • searchAllTransforms

        Summary:
        This method retrieves all datasets metadata, i.e., it does not retrieve the dataset content.

      • searchTransformContent

        com.google.gson.JsonObject searchTransformContent(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                                  int pageSize,
                                                  int currentPage)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - is the name of the dataset
        pageSize - is the number of tuples or registers returned per page. It is an optional parameter. If not present, the page size will be 20 tuples/registers.
        currentPage - is the page where the search will start. It is an optional parameter. If not present, the search operation will start from page zero.
        Returns:
        a page with some tuples or registers inside or an error if there is no such dataset. The current page is also returned to be used in future content requests.
        Summary:
        This method is responsible for retrieving pages of the dataset content
